and 5 share one root cause: no validated schema at the boundary. Untyped `req` (5) lets the unguarded parse (1) feed an unshaped `payload` into `validate`, where the unguarded deref (2) throws. That throw is then swallowed by the finding-3 catch (review-src/handler.ts:44), so a malformed request returns success-shaped `null` rather than crashing visibly -- 1, 2, and 3 compound into silent data corruption, not a clean failure. A single parse-and-validate step (zod/typed guard) at line 17 collapses 1, 2, 5, and Finding 7's type mismatch. Findings 4 (dead branch) and 6 (braces) are independent.\n\n### Missed surfaces (optional)\n\n`sendAuditLog` (line 57) is a no-op stub; even if Finding 4's dead branch were fixed, audit logging would silently do nothing -- worth a tracking issue.\n\n---\n\n**Verdict scope:** scope: api-correctness"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4387,"cache_read_input_tokens":65060,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4387},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75d4759c-66ec-4fa2-957e-08886534d41a","uuid":"678b8a0d-46cd-4a82-b273-62e86576fab1","request_id":"req_011CbrUWyZLUMAxMZLErnZCS"}
